The woman at the forefront of the design of Amir Khan's 24 carat gold shorts - the most expensive in sporting history - has detailed the process behind them ahead of the 28-year-old's world title bout against Devon Alexander on Saturday night.

Earlier this week it was revealed that Khan would be wearing the unique piece of clothing, worth around £30,000, when fighting against Alexander at the MGM Grand Garden in Las Vegas.

Sophie Whittam, designer of the shorts and creator of Fight Label, spoke in detail about the thinking behind the development of the shorts.

